data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Count
data.value: Counts the number of cells in a range that contain numbers.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.If
data.value: Checks whether a condition is met, and returns one value if TRUE, and another value if FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsNA
data.value: Checks whether a value is #N/A, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsError
data.value: Checks whether a value is an error (#N/A, #VALUE!, #REF!, #DIV/0!, #NUM!, #NAME?, or #NULL!), and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Sum
data.value: Adds all the numbers in a range of cells.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Average
data.value: Returns the average (arithmetic mean) of its arguments, which can be numbers or names, arrays, or references that contain numbers.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Min
data.value: Returns the smallest number in a set of values. Ignores logical values and text.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Max
data.value: Returns the largest value in a set of values. Ignores logical values and text.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Row
data.value: Returns the row number of a reference.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Column
data.value: Returns the column number of a reference.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NA
data.value: Returns the error value #N/A (value not available).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Npv
data.value: Returns the net present value of an investment based on a discount rate and a series of future payments (negative values) and income (positive values).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.StDev
data.value: Estimates standard deviation based on a sample (ignores logical values and text in the sample).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Dollar
data.value: Converts a number to text, using currency format.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Fixed
data.value: Rounds a number to the specified number of decimals and returns the result as text with or without commas.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Sin
data.value: Returns the sine of an angle.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Cos
data.value: Returns the cosine of an angle.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Tan
data.value: Returns the tangent of an angle.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ATan
data.value: Returns the arctangent of a number in radians, in the range -Pi/2 to Pi/2.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Pi
data.value: Returns the value of Pi, 3.14159265358979, accurate to 15 digits.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Sqrt
data.value: Returns the square root of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Exp
data.value: Returns e raised to the power of a given number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Ln
data.value: Returns the natural logarithm of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Log10
data.value: Returns the base-10 logarithm of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Abs
data.value: Returns the absolute value of a number, a number without its sign.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Int
data.value: Rounds a number down to the nearest integer.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Sign
data.value: Returns the sign of a number: 1 if the number is positive, zero if the number is zero, or -1 if the number is negative.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Round
data.value: Rounds a number to a specified number of digits.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Lookup
data.value: Looks up a value either from a one-row or one-column range or from an array. Provided for backward compatibility.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Index
data.value: Returns a value or reference of the cell at the intersection of a particular row and column, in a given range.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Rept
data.value: Repeats text a given number of times. Use REPT to fill a cell with a number of instances of a text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Mid
data.value: Returns the characters from the middle of a text string, given a starting position and length.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Len
data.value: Returns the number of characters in a text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Value
data.value: Converts a text string that represents a number to a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.True
data.value: Returns the logical value TRUE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.False
data.value: Returns the logical value FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.And
data.value: Checks whether all arguments are TRUE, and returns TRUE if all arguments are TRUE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Or
data.value: Checks whether any of the arguments are TRUE, and returns TRUE or FALSE. Returns FALSE only if all arguments are FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Not
data.value: Changes FALSE to TRUE, or TRUE to FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Mod
data.value: Returns the remainder after a number is divided by a divisor.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DCount
data.value: Counts the cells containing numbers in the field (column) of records in the database that match the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DSum
data.value: Adds the numbers in the field (column) of records in the database that match the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DAverage
data.value: Averages the values in a column in a list or database that match conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DMin
data.value: Returns the smallest number in the field (column) of records in the database that match the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DMax
data.value: Returns the largest number in the field (column) of records in the database that match the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DStDev
data.value: Estimates the standard deviation based on a sample from selected database entries.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Var
data.value: Estimates variance based on a sample (ignores logical values and text in the sample).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DVar
data.value: Estimates variance based on a sample from selected database entries.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Text
data.value: Converts a value to text in a specific number format.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Linest
data.value: Returns statistics that describe a linear trend matching known data points, by fitting a straight line using the least squares method.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Trend
data.value: Returns numbers in a linear trend matching known data points, using the least squares method.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Logest
data.value: Returns statistics that describe an exponential curve matching known data points.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Growth
data.value: Returns numbers in an exponential growth trend matching known data points.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Pv
data.value: Returns the present value of an investment: the total amount that a series of future payments is worth now.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Fv
data.value: Returns the future value of an investment based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NPer
data.value: Returns the number of periods for an investment based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Pmt
data.value: Calculates the payment for a loan based on constant payments and a constant interest rate.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Rate
data.value: Returns the interest rate per period of a loan or an investment. For example, use 6%/4 for quarterly payments at 6% APR.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Mirr
data.value: Returns the internal rate of return for a series of periodic cash flows, considering both cost of investment and interest on reinvestment of cash.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Irr
data.value: Returns the internal rate of return for a series of cash flows.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Rand
data.value: Returns a random number greater than or equal to 0 and less than 1, evenly distributed (changes on recalculation).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Match
data.value: Returns the relative position of an item in an array that matches a specified value in a specified order.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Date
data.value: Returns the number that represents the date in Spreadsheet date-time code.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Time
data.value: Converts hours, minutes, and seconds given as numbers to an Spreadsheet serial number, formatted with a time format.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Day
data.value: Returns the day of the month, a number from 1 to 31.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Month
data.value: Returns the month, a number from 1 (January) to 12 (December).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Year
data.value: Returns the year of a date, an integer in the range 1900 - 9999.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.WeekDay
data.value: Returns a number from 1 to 7 identifying the day of the week of a date.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Hour
data.value: Returns the hour as a number from 0 (12:00 A.M.) to 23 (11:00 P.M.).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Minute
data.value: Returns the minute, a number from 0 to 59.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Second
data.value: Returns the second, a number from 0 to 59.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Now
data.value: Returns the current date and time formatted as a date and time.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Areas
data.value: Returns the number of areas in a reference. An area is a range of contiguous cells or a single cell.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Rows
data.value: Returns the number of rows in a reference or array.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Columns
data.value: Returns the number of columns in an array or reference.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Offset
data.value: Returns a reference to a range that is a given number of rows and columns from a given reference.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Search
data.value: Returns the number of the character at which a specific character or text string is first found, reading left to right (not case-sensitive).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Transpose
data.value: Converts a vertical range of cells to a horizontal range, or vice versa.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Type
data.value: Returns an integer representing the data type of a value: number = 1; text = 2; logical value = 4; error value = 16; array = 64.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ATan2
data.value: Returns the arctangent of the specified x- and y- coordinates, in radians between -Pi and Pi, excluding -Pi.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ASin
data.value: Returns the arcsine of a number in radians, in the range -Pi/2 to Pi/2.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ACos
data.value: Returns the arccosine of a number, in radians in the range 0 to Pi. The arccosine is the angle whose cosine is Number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Choose
data.value: Chooses a value or action to perform from a list of values, based on an index number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.HLookup
data.value: Looks for a value in the top row of a table or array of values and returns the value in the same column from a row you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.VLookup
data.value: Looks for a value in the leftmost column of a table, and then returns a value in the same row from a column you specify. By default, the table must be sorted in an ascending order.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsRef
data.value: Checks whether a value is a reference, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Log
data.value: Returns the logarithm of a number to the base you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Char
data.value: Returns the character specified by the code number from the character set for your computer.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Lower
data.value: Converts all letters in a text string to lowercase.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Upper
data.value: Converts a text string to all uppercase letters.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Proper
data.value: Converts a text string to proper case; the first letter in each word in uppercase, and all other letters to lowercase.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Left
data.value: Returns the specified number of characters from the start of a text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Right
data.value: Returns the specified number of characters from the end of a text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Exact
data.value: Checks whether two text strings are exactly the same, and returns TRUE or FALSE. EXACT is case-sensitive.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Trim
data.value: Removes all spaces from a text string except for single spaces between words.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Replace
data.value: Replaces part of a text string with a different text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Substitute
data.value: Replaces existing text with new text in a text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Code
data.value: Returns a numeric code for the first character in a text string, in the character set used by your computer.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Find
data.value: Returns the starting position of one text string within another text string. FIND is case-sensitive.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Cell
data.value: Returns information about the formatting, location, or contents of the first cell, according to the sheet's reading order, in a reference.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsErr
data.value: Checks whether a value is an error (#VALUE!, #REF!, #DIV/0!, #NUM!, #NAME?, or #NULL!) excluding #N/A, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsText
data.value: Checks whether a value is text, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsNumber
data.value: Checks whether a value is a number, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsBlank
data.value: Checks whether a reference is to an empty cell, and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.T
data.value: Checks whether a value is text, and returns the text if it is, or returns double quotes (empty text) if it is not.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.N
data.value: Converts non-number value to a number, dates to serial numbers, TRUE to 1, anything else to 0 (zero).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DateValue
data.value: Converts a date in the form of text to a number that represents the date in Spreadsheet date-time code.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.TimeValue
data.value: Converts a text time to an Spreadsheet serial number for a time, a number from 0 (12:00:00 AM) to 0.999988426 (11:59:59 PM). Format the number with a time format after entering the formula.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Sln
data.value: Returns the straight-line depreciation of an asset for one period.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Syd
data.value: Returns the sum-of-years' digits depreciation of an asset for a specified period.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Ddb
data.value: Returns the depreciation of an asset for a specified period using the double-declining balance method or some other method you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Indirect
data.value: Returns the reference specified by a text string.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Call
data.value: Calls a procedure in a dynamic link library or code resource.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Clean
data.value: Removes all nonprintable characters from text.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.MDeterm
data.value: Returns the matrix determinant of an array.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.MInverse
data.value: Returns the inverse matrix for the matrix stored in an array.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.MMult
data.value: Returns the matrix product of two arrays, an array with the same number of rows as array1 and columns as array2.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Ipmt
data.value: Returns the interest payment for a given period for an investment, based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Ppmt
data.value: Returns the payment on the principal for a given investment based on periodic, constant payments and a constant interest rate.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.CountA
data.value: Counts the number of cells in a range that are not empty.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Product
data.value: Multiplies all the numbers given as arguments.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Fact
data.value: Returns the factorial of a number, equal to 1*2*3*...* Number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DProduct
data.value: Multiplies the values in the field (column) of records in the database that match the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsNonText
data.value: Checks whether a value is not text (blank cells are not text), and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.StDevP
data.value: Calculates standard deviation based on the entire population given as arguments (ignores logical values and text).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.VarP
data.value: Calculates variance based on the entire population (ignores logical values and text in the population).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DStDevP
data.value: Calculates the standard deviation based on the entire population of selected database entries.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DVarP
data.value: Calculates variance based on the entire population of selected database entries.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Trunc
data.value: Truncates a number to an integer by removing the decimal, or fractional, part of the number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.IsLogical
data.value: Checks whether a value is a logical value (TRUE or FALSE), and returns TRUE or FALSE.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DCountA
data.value: Counts nonblank cells in the field (column) of records in the database that match the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.FindB
data.value: Finds the starting position of one text string within another text string. FINDB is case-sensitive. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.SearchB
data.value: Returns the number of the character at which a specific character or text string is first found, reading left to right (not case-sensitive). Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ReplaceB
data.value: Replaces part of a text string with a different text string. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.LeftB
data.value: Returns the specified number of characters from the start of a text string. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.RightB
data.value: Returns the specified number of characters from the end of a text string. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.MidB
data.value: Returns characters from the middle of a text string, given a starting position and length. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.LenB
data.value: Returns the number of characters in a text string. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.RoundUp
data.value: Rounds a number up, away from zero.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.RoundDown
data.value: Rounds a number down, toward zero.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Asc
data.value: Changes full-width (double-byte) characters to half-width (single-byte) characters. Use with double-byte character sets (DBCS).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Rank
data.value: Returns the rank of a number in a list of numbers: its size relative to other values in the list.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Address
data.value: Creates a cell reference as text, given specified row and column numbers.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Days360
data.value: Returns the number of days between two dates based on a 360-day year (twelve 30-day months).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Today
data.value: Returns the current date formatted as a date.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Vdb
data.value: Returns the depreciation of an asset for any period you specify, including partial periods, using the double-declining balance method or some other method you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Median
data.value: Returns the median, or the number in the middle of the set of given numbers.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.SumProduct
data.value: Returns the sum of the products of corresponding ranges or arrays.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.SinH
data.value: Returns the hyperbolic sine of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.CosH
data.value: Returns the hyperbolic cosine of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.TanH
data.value: Returns the hyperbolic tangent of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ASinH
data.value: Returns the inverse hyperbolic sine of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ACosH
data.value: Returns the inverse hyperbolic cosine of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ATanH
data.value: Returns the inverse hyperbolic tangent of a number.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.DGet
data.value: Extracts from a database a single record that matches the conditions you specify.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Info
data.value: Returns information about the current operating environment.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Db
data.value: Returns the depreciation of an asset for a specified period using the fixed-declining balance method.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Frequency
data.value: Calculates how often values occur within a range of values and then returns a vertical array of numbers having one more element than Bins_array.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ErrorType
data.value: Returns a number matching an error value.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.RegisterId
data.value: Returns the register ID of the specified dynamic link library (DLL) or code resource that has been previously registered.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Avedev
data.value: Returns the average of the absolute deviations of data points from their mean. Arguments can be numbers or names, arrays, or references that contain numbers.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.BetaDistCompatibility
data.value: Returns the cumulative beta probability density function.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.GammaLn
data.value: Returns the natural logarithm of the gamma function.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.BetaInv
data.value: Returns the inverse of the cumulative beta probability density function (BETADIST).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.BinomDist
data.value: Returns the individual term binomial distribution probability.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ChiDist
data.value: Returns the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ChiInv
data.value: Returns the inverse of the right-tailed probability of the chi-squared distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Combin
data.value: Returns the number of combinations for a given number of items.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Confidence
data.value: Returns the confidence interval for a population mean, using a normal distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.CritBinom
data.value: Returns the smallest value for which the cumulative binomial distribution is greater than or equal to a criterion value.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Even
data.value: Rounds a positive number up and negative number down to the nearest even integer.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.ExponDist
data.value: Returns the exponential distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.FDist
data.value: Returns the (right-tailed) F probability distribution (degree of diversity) for two data sets.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.FInv
data.value: Returns the inverse of the (right-tailed) F probability distribution: if p = FDIST(x,...), then FINV(p,...) = x.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Fisher
data.value: Returns the Fisher transformation.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.FisherInv
data.value: Returns the inverse of the Fisher transformation: if y = FISHER(x), then FISHERINV(y) = x.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Floor
data.value: Rounds a number down to the nearest multiple of significance.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.GammaDist
data.value: Returns the gamma distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.GammaInv
data.value: Returns the inverse of the gamma cumulative distribution: if p = GAMMADIST(x,...), then GAMMAINV(p,...) = x.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Ceiling
data.value: Rounds a number up, to the nearest multiple of significance.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.HypGeomDist
data.value: Returns the hypergeometric distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.LogNormDistCompatibility
data.value: Returns the cumulative lognormal distribution of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with parameters Mean and Standard_dev.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.LogInvCompatibility
data.value: Returns the inverse of the lognormal cumulative distribution function of x, where ln(x) is normally distributed with parameters Mean and Standard_dev.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NegBinomDist
data.value: Returns the negative binomial distribution, the probability that there will be Number_f failures before the Number_s-th success, with Probability_s probability of a success.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NormDistCompatibility
data.value: Returns the normal cumulative distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NormSDistCompatibility
data.value: Returns the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NormInvCompatibility
data.value: Returns the inverse of the normal cumulative distribution for the specified mean and standard deviation.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.NormSInvCompatibility
data.value: Returns the inverse of the standard normal cumulative distribution (has a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one).

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Standardize
data.value: Returns a normalized value from a distribution characterized by a mean and standard deviation.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Odd
data.value: Rounds a positive number up and negative number down to the nearest odd integer.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Permut
data.value: Returns the number of permutations for a given number of objects that can be selected from the total objects.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Poisson
data.value: Returns the Poisson distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.TDist
data.value: Returns the Student's t-distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.Weibull
data.value: Returns the Weibull distribution.

data.name: XtraSpreadsheetFunctionDescriptionStringId.SumXMY2
data.value: Sums the squares of the differences in two corresponding ranges or arrays.
